title: 820-4924 liquid damage, light on charger, trackpad clicks, no chime
message:
Liquid damage.
Burned our keyboard backlight connector, U8330 with burned out paths around (dont care about keyboard backlight).

LCD connector burned out as well.


Got light on charger, no chime, USB light is ON, caps lock LED don’t react, blank screen (on ext display no image as well).

PPBUS_G3H - 12.57V
PPBUS_S5_HS_COMPUTING - 12.58V
PPBUS_S5_HS_OTHER5V - 12.58V
PPBUS_S5_HS_OTHER3V3 - 12.58V
PPVIN_S4_TPAD - 
PP3V42_G3H - 3.43V
PPVRTC_G3H - 3.32V
PP5V_S5 - 5.01V
PP5V_S4 - 0V

PP3V3_S5 - 3.32V
PP3V3_S4 - 0V

And I am lost as PM_SLP_S5_L etc is a nightmare for me.

Any help?

title: 820-4924 liquid damage, light on charger, trackpad clicks, no chime
message:

title: 820-4924 liquid damage, light on charger, trackpad clicks, no chime
message:
"PM_BATLOW_L - 0.035V"
PCH cannot start power on sequence then.
Be sure to use original 60/85W Magsafe 2 charger.
